Cape Benchmark Stats - Generate JSON statistics for all benchmarks and submissions

Usage:
  cape benchmark stats

Description:
  Generates comprehensive JSON statistics for all benchmarks and their submissions.
  The output includes performance metrics for each submission grouped by benchmark,
  making it suitable for generating summary tables and reports.

Output Format:
  The command outputs JSON with the following structure:
  {
    "generated_at": "2025-08-20T12:00:00Z",
    "benchmarks": [
      {
        "name": "fibonacci",
        "submission_count": 3,
        "submissions": [
          {
            "compiler": "Plinth",
            "version": "1.52.0.0",
            "author": "Unisay",
            "date": "2025-08-18",
            "timestamp": "2025-08-18T16:56:26Z",
            "cpu_units": 117422538753,
            "cpu_units_formatted": "117.42B",
            "memory_units": 437984037,
            "memory_units_formatted": "437.98M",
            "script_size": 45,
            "term_size": 38,
            "submission_dir": "Plinth_1.52.0.0_Unisay"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }

Fields:
  - compiler: Name of the compiler used
  - version: Version of the compiler
  - author: Contributor/author of the submission
  - date: Date of submission (YYYY-MM-DD)
  - cpu_units: Raw CPU units consumed
  - cpu_units_formatted: Human-readable CPU units (B=billions, M=millions, K=thousands)
  - memory_units: Raw memory units consumed
  - memory_units_formatted: Human-readable memory units
  - script_size: Size of the UPLC script in bytes
  - term_size: Size of the term
  - submission_dir: Directory name of the submission

Examples:
  # Generate stats for all benchmarks
  cape benchmark stats

  # Save stats to a file
  cape benchmark stats > benchmark-stats.json

  # Use with jq to extract specific data
  cape benchmark stats | jq '.benchmarks[] | select(.name=="fibonacci")'

Notes:
  - Benchmarks without submissions will have an empty submissions array
  - Numbers are formatted for display (e.g., 117.42B for billions)
  - Raw values are also included for programmatic use